---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Battle Buddies Privacy Policy — Carson Underwood"
  description="Privacy policy for the Battle Buddies iOS and watchOS app."
>
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800 p-8 shadow-xl">
    <h1 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100">Battle Buddies — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 font-mono text-xs text-slate-500">Last updated: July 13, 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
      <section>
        <p>
          Battle Buddies is designed so that <strong class="text-slate-100">I (the developer) never
          see your data</strong>. There is no server, no analytics service, and no account system
          operated by me. This app-specific policy supplements my
          <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-cyan-400 hover:underline">general privacy policy</a>
          and takes precedence for Battle Buddies where they differ.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">What the App Reads</h2>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li class="flex gap-2 text-slate-400"><span class="text-cyan-500 select-none">›</span><span><strong class="text-slate-300">Health data</strong> (with your permission): workouts, steps, stand time, mindful minutes, and sleep — read on your device, only to award XP to your character. The app never writes to Health in normal use.</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-2 text-slate-400"><span class="text-cyan-500 select-none">›</span><span><strong class="text-slate-300">Manual activity logs</strong> you enter by hand.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Where Your Data Lives</h2>
        <p>
          On your devices, and in <strong class="text-slate-100">your private iCloud
          database</strong> (synced by Apple's CloudKit under your Apple ID). Apple's iCloud terms
          apply; I have no access to it. Raw health data never leaves your device — only derived XP
          awards and your character's stats are stored and synced.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">What Buddies Can See</h2>
        <p>
          When you connect with a buddy via an invite link, a shared zone in iCloud holds: your
          character summary (name, sprite, level, streak, attribute XP totals, recent-week XP
          total), nudges, duels, and battle records between the two of you. Buddies never see raw
          health data, individual activities, or anything about your other buddies. Removing a
          buddy deletes the shared zone.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Notifications</h2>
        <p>
          All notifications are generated on your device. Silent CloudKit pushes wake the app to
          sync; anything visible is composed locally and can be disabled per category in Settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          Battle Buddies does not integrate with any third-party analytics, advertising, or data
          collection services. The only service involved is Apple's iCloud/CloudKit, under your own
          Apple ID.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Deleting Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          Settings → Account → <strong class="text-slate-100">Delete Buddy &amp; All Data</strong>
          removes your character, activity history, buddy connections (including shared zones), and
          the synced copy in your iCloud database. Health data is managed by iOS and is never
          stored by the app.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Battle Buddies does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children
          under the age of 13.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          If this policy changes in the future, the updated version will be posted at this URL with
          a revised "last updated" date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this privacy policy, you can reach me at
          <a href="/contact" class="text-cyan-400 hover:underline">cunderw.dev/contact</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
